item.dc:creator: Goxenar
item.description:
Thanks a lot man, to explain the poll, to be honest I feel as if Dubstep in the Auxy community is underrated, but I wanted the opinion of the community itself on that.

Sure, I‚Äôve had a few songs reposted by Auxy, but I feel as if Dubstep just doesn‚Äôt take the spot of most of the songs in the Auxy application feed.

Here, let me explain a bit more.

The songs in which get posted within the Auxy application feed are TOP knotch. I absolutely love them. Mr. Anderson‚Äôs the Heavens is a good example, Blackocean‚Äôs Crimson is another good example, but when will a Dubstep track reach that spot?

In all honesty, creating Dubstep in Auxy consists of an INTENSE amount of creativity, definitely patience and well, some basic Dubstep knowledge, yet it seems as if it can never reach the spot of ‚ÄúFeatured Track.‚Äù

It always seems like it gets a ‚Äúhere here, I like this, but lets not give it too much support now.‚Äù
